e <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>General<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> section, set the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Platform Toolset<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Visual Studio 2013 (v120)<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[6661,6828],"source":" To configure this setting in your project, open the project's properties and in the **General** section, set the **Platform Toolset** to **Visual Studio 2013 (v120)**."},{"content":"If you install the Phone 8.0 tools in Visual Studio setup, you can also target Windows Phone 8.0.","pos":[6835,6932]},{"content":"A new concept introduced in Windows 10 called API Contracts replaces the old practice of targeting specific Windows versions.","pos":[6939,7064]},{"content":"Instead, you can choose which API Contracts your app needs and it will then run on any Windows device that supports those contracts.","pos":[7065,7197]},{"content":"An API contract is a set of stable APIs that provide access to platform or device resources.","pos":[7198,7290]},{"content":"API Contracts can be included as references in the project system.","pos":[7291,7357]},{"content":"In a Visual Studio project, if you add a reference to a particular Extension SDK, then Visual Studio adds the appropriate API Contracts.","pos":[7358,7494]},{"pos":[7501,7633],"content":"For more information on all of these concepts, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Guide to Windows Universal Apps<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=534605)</ept>.","source":"For more information on all of these concepts, see [Guide to Windows Universal Apps](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=534605)."},{"pos":[7668,7709],"content":"Desktop, Server, and Cloud Apps and Games"},{"content":"In the cloud you can write Azure native code assemblies in C++ and call into them from Web Roles that are created in C#.","pos":[7713,7833]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure SDK<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=256416)</ept>.","pos":[7834,7921],"so